                <note rend="inline" type="source">311.6121 Gorin, M. N./48: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-03-26T20:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 26, 1941—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>366. Your 574, March 23, 9 p.m. Department is informed by Justice that Gorin paid
                    his fine of $10,000 in addition to costs amounting to approximately $1400 in
                    cash upon his release. The suspension of his fine was never requested nor
                    considered. We shall continue here to press upon the Ambassador the importance
                    of the release of all American citizens and the granting of permission for the
                    wives and children of American citizens to leave the country.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
